WEBVTT

00:05.296 --> 00:06.006
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:07.090 --> 00:09.426
<i>Noah Gorman, 19 years old.</i>

00:09.426 --> 00:11.553
<i>His eyes were stapled open.</i>

00:11.553 --> 00:12.846
This was sadistic.

00:12.846 --> 00:16.349
<i>Someone got pleasure
out of torturing him.</i>

00:16.349 --> 00:18.768
Noah came out as gay
two months ago.

00:18.768 --> 00:20.353
His family kicked him out.

00:20.353 --> 00:23.898
They said that Noah
is no longer their son.

00:23.898 --> 00:26.109
Any leads on Noah's abductor?

00:26.109 --> 00:27.318
No, not yet.

00:27.318 --> 00:29.029
<i>But there will be.</i>

00:29.029 --> 00:31.531
Who the hell are you?

00:31.531 --> 00:35.118
I'm gonna be right here until
you're able to talk to me.

00:35.118 --> 00:36.369
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:36.369 --> 00:38.663
He had nowhere to go.

00:45.670 --> 00:47.255
<i>- Stop! No!</i>

00:50.216 --> 00:53.345
[footsteps thud]

01:00.101 --> 01:03.271
[sniffling]

01:15.241 --> 01:16.743
I'm sorry, the nightmares.

01:16.743 --> 01:17.911
Oh, it's okay.

01:17.911 --> 01:19.162
Just got home.

01:19.162 --> 01:20.372
Can I get you something?

01:20.372 --> 01:21.331
No, I'm just gonna
get a water.

01:21.331 --> 01:22.374
Let me get it for you--

01:22.374 --> 01:23.792
I'll do it myself, thanks.

01:32.509 --> 01:35.637
[siren wails distantly]

01:44.854 --> 01:46.398
<i>Ah!</i>

01:55.532 --> 01:56.825
[shouts]

01:59.285 --> 02:01.287
- [sighs]
- [coughs]

02:05.166 --> 02:06.668
[whimpers]

02:10.005 --> 02:11.798
Sorry.

02:11.798 --> 02:13.174
It's okay.

02:24.352 --> 02:25.687
[breathes shakily]

02:35.030 --> 02:37.240
You know, those--
those resources I mentioned--

02:37.240 --> 02:38.867
I don't want them.

02:38.867 --> 02:40.493
Okay.

02:40.493 --> 02:43.163
I just want to forget.

02:43.163 --> 02:46.207
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

02:46.207 --> 02:48.710
I want to sleep.

02:48.710 --> 02:54.007
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:54.007 --> 02:58.136
Well, you change your mind,
you just let me know.

02:58.136 --> 03:00.263
And they do work.

03:00.263 --> 03:07.395
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:28.917 --> 03:30.418
[sighs]

03:34.381 --> 03:35.924
[sighs]

03:38.176 --> 03:40.720
- Hey.
- Hey.

03:40.720 --> 03:43.098
Pulled an all-nighter,
figured you'd be here.

03:43.098 --> 03:45.141
[grunts]
Thanks.

03:45.141 --> 03:46.685
Anything?

03:48.937 --> 03:50.313
No.

03:52.190 --> 03:53.483
And Noah?

03:55.944 --> 03:59.447
Hasn't said a word
about what happened to him.

03:59.447 --> 04:01.324
Still having nightmares.

04:02.659 --> 04:04.869
Who wouldn't, I suppose.

04:04.869 --> 04:07.122
I got a detail
sitting on my house,

04:07.122 --> 04:09.916
keeping an eye on him.

04:09.916 --> 04:12.043
It's like there's
no life in him yet.

04:12.043 --> 04:14.379
There will be.

04:14.379 --> 04:17.507
We see it every day.
People recover.

04:21.469 --> 04:24.764
He can't stay at your house
forever, Hank.

04:24.764 --> 04:28.435
It's gonna make the case
complicated for the jury.

04:28.435 --> 04:30.562
It's just
till he gets better.

04:32.355 --> 04:34.816
He's still refusing support.

04:34.816 --> 04:37.110
Hey, our investigative alert
on Noah popped.

04:37.110 --> 04:38.695
What do we got?

04:38.695 --> 04:40.613
A body.

04:40.613 --> 04:43.283
Chances are, the thing
washed up a while ago.

04:43.283 --> 04:45.035
This stretch doesn't get
much foot traffic

04:45.035 --> 04:46.911
during this time of year.

04:46.911 --> 04:48.121
So who spotted it?

04:48.121 --> 04:49.372
One of ours.

04:49.372 --> 04:50.665
He was patrolling
near the shore,

04:50.665 --> 04:52.167
clocked it from afar.

04:52.167 --> 04:55.045
The barrel could have gotten
dislodged from elsewhere

04:55.045 --> 04:57.213
or just floated up
from the depths here.

04:57.213 --> 04:58.715
- Huh.
- Either way,

04:58.715 --> 05:00.467
it's been in the water a while.

05:00.467 --> 05:01.634
As soon as we logged
the body in,

05:01.634 --> 05:04.012
your investigative alert
popped.

05:04.012 --> 05:06.431
You found it like this?

05:06.431 --> 05:07.724
Right there at the waterline.

05:07.724 --> 05:09.476
We just pulled it to shore.

05:09.476 --> 05:12.854
<i>[tense music]</i>

05:12.854 --> 05:19.861
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:36.961 --> 05:37.379
[saw buzzing]

05:40.090 --> 05:43.009
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

05:43.009 --> 05:50.016
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:03.571 --> 06:05.657
They were in that water
for some time.

06:05.657 --> 06:08.410
The cold kept them preserved.

06:08.410 --> 06:09.994
Guess we can count
ourselves lucky there,

06:09.994 --> 06:12.163
but there's no way
I'll be able to tell you

06:12.163 --> 06:13.456
exact time of death.

06:13.456 --> 06:16.084
Best guess?

06:16.084 --> 06:18.378
One to three months.

06:18.378 --> 06:20.088
They're both young.

06:20.088 --> 06:22.424
guessing Jane Doe 1
is a teenager.

06:22.424 --> 06:24.634
The other can't be
older than 25.

06:24.634 --> 06:26.553
We're rushing dental
and prints,

06:26.553 --> 06:28.013
should have IDs for you soon.

06:28.013 --> 06:29.389
And the wounds?

06:29.389 --> 06:31.391
Got signs of bindings
on both--

06:31.391 --> 06:33.560
wrists, ankles.

06:33.560 --> 06:37.939
Jane Doe 2 has bruising
around her stomach.

06:37.939 --> 06:39.983
There are six stab wounds
on each.

06:39.983 --> 06:41.568
The stab wounds
are placed to avoid

06:41.568 --> 06:43.820
any major organs, arteries.

06:43.820 --> 06:46.448
Placed so they'd
bleed out slow.

06:49.576 --> 06:52.287
I'll know more
once the autopsy is done.

06:52.287 --> 06:54.122
You staying for the full?

07:00.045 --> 07:01.546
Yeah, any companies
that manufacture

07:01.546 --> 07:03.214
those oil barrels, all years.

07:03.214 --> 07:04.424
Thanks.

07:04.424 --> 07:06.384
Izzy and Maria Pereda.

07:06.384 --> 07:09.596
They're sisters.
Izzy was 18, Maria 20.

07:09.596 --> 07:11.264
Chicago locals.

07:11.264 --> 07:12.766
Anyone report them missing?

07:12.766 --> 07:15.060
No, but Izzy had
a short sheet.

07:15.060 --> 07:17.771
She was popped once
for prostitution,

07:17.771 --> 07:19.981
once for possession.

07:23.151 --> 07:28.406
Every wound the sisters have
are exact matches with Noah's.

07:28.406 --> 07:32.077
So we're saying
we have a serial killer?

07:32.077 --> 07:33.787
Just brief the team.

07:33.787 --> 07:36.498
Call in Chapman.
I'll loop in a profiler.

07:36.498 --> 07:38.750
CPD has a profiler?

07:38.750 --> 07:41.002
No, not officially.

07:44.339 --> 07:47.092
If she's not at her desk,
then she should be back here.

07:47.092 --> 07:50.011
She thinks if you dull
the senses, it helps you focus.

07:50.011 --> 07:51.471
- Huh.
- Right through there.

07:51.471 --> 07:53.098
Good luck.
- Thanks.

07:59.062 --> 08:00.563
[knocking on door]

08:03.942 --> 08:05.694
Detective Petrovic?

08:07.445 --> 08:09.614
Hello?

08:09.614 --> 08:12.659
Excuse me, Detective Petrovic?

08:12.659 --> 08:14.536
[groans]

08:16.663 --> 08:18.832
Sergeant Hank Voight,
Intelligence.

08:18.832 --> 08:20.583
Y-you have a juvenile case?

08:20.583 --> 08:22.711
Actually,
I've got a serial killer.

08:22.711 --> 08:24.754
Chicago has
no active serial killers,

08:24.754 --> 08:26.089
and I don't work cold cases.
- No, this is active.

08:26.089 --> 08:27.507
It's not a beneficial use
of my time.

08:27.507 --> 08:29.259
- It's just new.
- I would have heard.

08:29.259 --> 08:31.136
It hasn't been released yet.

08:31.136 --> 08:32.887
<i>[tense music]</i>

08:32.887 --> 08:35.598
Look, I-I've got three bodies.

08:35.598 --> 08:41.187
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:41.187 --> 08:42.772
Three?

08:46.276 --> 08:53.241
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:57.746 --> 08:59.622
I can feel you assessing me.

08:59.622 --> 09:00.999
It's distracting.

09:00.999 --> 09:02.167
Please stop.

09:04.961 --> 09:06.046
Yeah.

09:06.046 --> 09:07.672
These wounds
are far too concise

09:07.672 --> 09:08.715
to be coincidental.

09:08.715 --> 09:10.258
Depth, wound type--

09:10.258 --> 09:12.427
it's the same offender.

09:12.427 --> 09:13.928
And his profile?

09:13.928 --> 09:17.390
You do know I'm not
a certified profiler.

09:17.390 --> 09:18.725
I've heard your reputation.

09:18.725 --> 09:22.103
Mm, and I've heard yours too.

09:22.103 --> 09:23.271
Can't all be true.

09:27.192 --> 09:28.610
Okay.

09:30.487 --> 09:32.405
On first thought--

09:32.405 --> 09:35.909
which, to be clear,
is a thought and is my first--

09:35.909 --> 09:39.996
these crimes are motivated
by a pleasure in pain, sadism.

09:39.996 --> 09:41.706
The offender is organized.

09:41.706 --> 09:43.333
This guy will have a job.

09:43.333 --> 09:44.334
He'll appear stable.

09:44.334 --> 09:45.794
He's above average
intelligence.

09:45.794 --> 09:47.587
Doesn't appear
sexually motivated,

09:47.587 --> 09:49.464
but that's harder to pinpoint.

09:49.464 --> 09:51.424
Power and control
can be sexual.

09:51.424 --> 09:54.803
Uh, who was the first victim,
Noah, with?

09:56.680 --> 09:59.724
Noah was found alone.

09:59.724 --> 10:01.142
But he survived.

10:01.142 --> 10:03.645
He didn't tell you
who he was with?

10:05.397 --> 10:08.191
He hasn't been able
to tell us much of anything.

10:11.736 --> 10:13.196
Hmm.

10:13.196 --> 10:14.656
Well...

10:18.326 --> 10:22.205
The bindings on the sisters
are different.

10:22.205 --> 10:25.000
One was standing bound,
the other sitting.

10:25.000 --> 10:30.213
That's why there's bruising
on her stomach, ligatures.

10:30.213 --> 10:31.798
But the eyes...

10:33.174 --> 10:36.511
They were made
to watch each other bleed out,

10:36.511 --> 10:39.097
watch each other's pain.

10:40.557 --> 10:42.517
That's part of the why.

10:42.517 --> 10:46.396
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:46.396 --> 10:49.482
Noah wasn't alone.

10:49.482 --> 10:51.026
Hm.

10:54.029 --> 10:55.739
<i>The Mexican rain forest
serves as home</i>

10:55.739 --> 10:59.784
<i>to one of the loudest animals
on Earth, the howler monkey.</i>

10:59.784 --> 11:01.953
<i>Normally a youngling
of this size</i>

11:01.953 --> 11:03.496
<i>would be clutching
his mother's back.</i>

11:03.496 --> 11:04.914
Hey.

11:04.914 --> 11:06.458
<i>This little fella
is braving the treetops</i>

11:06.458 --> 11:09.419
<i>on his own today,
out for a spot of lunch.</i>

11:09.419 --> 11:12.255
<i>When fully grown,
the bone in its neck...</i>

11:12.255 --> 11:15.300
Noah, I want
to talk to you, okay?

11:15.300 --> 11:18.470
I'm gonna turn this down.
Is that all right?

11:18.470 --> 11:20.805
<i>This howl is used to warn...
[volume lowers]</i>

11:20.805 --> 11:22.474
Okay?

11:27.312 --> 11:28.855
[sighs]

11:28.855 --> 11:31.066
We found two bodies today.

11:33.068 --> 11:37.322
They were hurt...
in the same way you were.

11:38.823 --> 11:40.909
It's the same person.

11:40.909 --> 11:43.536
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:43.536 --> 11:46.581
I need to ask you a question
about that night.

11:46.581 --> 11:49.250
It's okay.
Hey, you're okay.

11:49.250 --> 11:50.585
You're safe.
- [sniffling]

11:50.585 --> 11:54.172
Hey, you're safe.
You're right here with me.

11:54.172 --> 11:55.715
You're okay.

11:55.715 --> 11:58.093
[breathes deeply]

11:58.093 --> 11:59.094
There.

11:59.094 --> 12:00.303
[sobs]

12:02.263 --> 12:04.474
Was somebody else
with you that night?

12:04.474 --> 12:06.226
Were you not alone?

12:06.226 --> 12:07.686
[sobs]

12:07.686 --> 12:09.396
All right, that's it.
Okay.

12:09.396 --> 12:10.772
Thank you.

12:12.148 --> 12:14.150
Who? Who was with you?

12:14.150 --> 12:15.443
Okay. okay.
No, no, no.

12:15.443 --> 12:16.778
- [hyperventilating]
- Hey, hey, we're done.

12:16.778 --> 12:17.946
We're done.
That's all we're gonna do.

12:17.946 --> 12:20.073
Easy, easy.
We're just gonna breathe.

12:20.073 --> 12:22.075
We're gonna breathe.
Hey, you're right here with me.

12:22.075 --> 12:23.535
Come on, breathe in.

12:23.535 --> 12:24.786
Come on.

12:24.786 --> 12:25.912
Nice and deep.
You can do it.

12:25.912 --> 12:27.205
There you go.

12:27.205 --> 12:29.290
That's it.
Let it go.

12:29.290 --> 12:31.960
- [exhales shakily]
- That's it. That's it.

12:31.960 --> 12:34.754
Come on, nice and deep,
nice and smooth.

12:34.754 --> 12:36.089
See? You're right here with me.

12:36.089 --> 12:37.716
You're okay.
You're safe.

12:37.716 --> 12:40.051
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:45.265 --> 12:46.558
Yeah, Noah seemed to be
confirming he wasn't alone,

12:47.392 --> 12:49.019
and then, I mean, he panicked.

12:49.019 --> 12:50.520
He said nothing else?

12:50.520 --> 12:53.273
No. Once he calmed down,
he fell asleep.

12:54.649 --> 12:56.192
I mean--

12:56.192 --> 12:58.194
I don't know how to press him
further without the panic.

12:58.194 --> 12:59.487
I mean, it's his instinct.

12:59.487 --> 13:02.574
His brain's still processing
what happened.

13:02.574 --> 13:04.868
Add to it that his parents
told him he'd be punished

13:04.868 --> 13:06.453
for being gay,
this kid probably thinks

13:06.453 --> 13:08.538
the hand of God hurt him,

13:08.538 --> 13:10.331
is resting on his shoulder.

13:12.167 --> 13:14.836
Detective
Josephine "Petrovick," SVU.

13:14.836 --> 13:17.213
Uh, Petrovic, but Jo.

13:17.213 --> 13:19.466
Yeah, she's gonna be helping
us out here while she can.

13:19.466 --> 13:21.718
All right, what do we have
on the Pereda sisters?

13:21.718 --> 13:24.471
Both girls were born and
raised in Chicago, West Side.

13:24.471 --> 13:26.431
Parents died
when they were young,

13:26.431 --> 13:27.682
have little family left.

13:27.682 --> 13:29.601
Mm-hmm, Izzy Pereda
was the youngest sister.

13:29.601 --> 13:31.019
She was addicted to heroin,

13:31.019 --> 13:33.146
and she worked as a prostitute
to support that habit.

13:33.146 --> 13:34.356
According
to their social media,

13:34.356 --> 13:35.774
the older sister, Maria,
was trying

13:35.774 --> 13:37.984
to get her out of that life,
but was unsuccessful.

13:37.984 --> 13:39.944
Izzy clearly loved her sister,

13:39.944 --> 13:41.571
but her last arrest
was only two months ago.

13:41.571 --> 13:43.323
Right before
they both disappeared.

13:43.323 --> 13:45.992
Credit card usage,
social media, all telephone,

13:45.992 --> 13:47.660
everything stopped
for both sisters

13:47.660 --> 13:48.995
exactly two months ago.

13:48.995 --> 13:50.872
That's when we believe
they were taken.

13:50.872 --> 13:52.165
All right,
any connect to Noah?

13:52.165 --> 13:53.583
Nothing concrete.

13:53.583 --> 13:57.170
All have little family,
few to report them missing.

13:57.170 --> 13:59.381
It's possible that Noah
was selling himself.

13:59.381 --> 14:01.508
Possible sex work
is our connect.

14:01.508 --> 14:03.760
Perpetrator could easily be
a john or a pimp.

14:03.760 --> 14:05.512
Hm.

14:05.512 --> 14:07.180
All right,
what about the barrels?

14:07.180 --> 14:09.015
What do we got there?
- No prints or DNA.

14:09.015 --> 14:10.183
They were in the water
too long.

14:10.183 --> 14:11.601
And those barrels are generic.

14:11.601 --> 14:12.894
They're manufactured en masse.

14:12.894 --> 14:15.021
I got something.
When Izzy Pereda was popped

14:15.021 --> 14:16.773
for prostitution,
she was bailed out

14:16.773 --> 14:18.316
by this guy right here.

14:18.316 --> 14:19.818
This is Manuel Tovar,
known to Vice.

14:19.818 --> 14:21.903
He's a working Romeo pimp.
Lives with his girls,

14:21.903 --> 14:23.530
never lets 'em
out of his sight.

14:23.530 --> 14:26.032
Uh, he uses a website
to attract johns.

14:26.032 --> 14:27.909
Now, he's got no priors
for assault,

14:27.909 --> 14:31.538
but, uh, Vice was pretty clear,
he's with those girls 24-7.

14:31.538 --> 14:34.040
So if our offender
followed the same MO,

14:34.040 --> 14:35.375
stalked and abducted Izzy--

14:35.375 --> 14:37.085
Chances are, at the very
least, he saw something.

14:37.085 --> 14:38.211
All right, let's go.

14:38.211 --> 14:39.838
We know where he lives?
- Yeah.

14:39.838 --> 14:42.841
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:42.841 --> 14:49.556
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:50.640 --> 14:51.766
All right, we're up.

14:51.766 --> 14:53.643
Torres, I got eyes on you.

14:53.643 --> 14:55.478
We play it nice and steady.

14:55.478 --> 14:59.274
<i>There's no way Tovar
talks to us without charges.</i>

14:59.274 --> 15:02.318
<i>Just stay hidden
until cash is exchanged.</i>

15:02.318 --> 15:04.738
Copy that.
I'm in.

15:04.738 --> 15:08.116
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:08.116 --> 15:09.659
Room's empty.

15:15.290 --> 15:17.500
Tovar's girl we hired
isn't here yet.

15:17.500 --> 15:18.752
Copy you, Torres.

15:18.752 --> 15:22.172
No sign of the girl or Tovar
on the east side.

15:25.592 --> 15:27.510
I got something.

15:27.510 --> 15:29.929
<i>I got a male
headed your way, Torres.</i>

15:29.929 --> 15:31.681
<i>Looks like security.</i>

15:34.809 --> 15:37.687
Can I help you?

15:37.687 --> 15:39.606
- You Eddie?
- Yeah.

15:39.606 --> 15:41.024
Put your hands out.

15:41.024 --> 15:42.442
Now.

15:43.651 --> 15:46.613
- I'm clean.
- No drugs, alcohol?

15:46.613 --> 15:47.947
Gonna party
with your girlfriend?

15:47.947 --> 15:49.824
No.

15:49.824 --> 15:51.618
What's your full name, Eddie?

15:51.618 --> 15:54.079
I'm not--I'm not
telling you my full name.

15:54.079 --> 15:55.455
Yes, you are.

15:55.455 --> 15:56.998
No, I'm not.

15:58.500 --> 16:00.377
Okay?

16:00.377 --> 16:01.586
I--

16:03.380 --> 16:05.256
I booked a girl online,
and you already know that,

16:05.256 --> 16:07.759
so we don't have to do
all the 20 questions.

16:13.139 --> 16:14.849
We good or not?

16:14.849 --> 16:20.522
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:20.522 --> 16:22.607
Here they are.

16:22.607 --> 16:25.777
Yeah, I got a positive
on Tovar.

16:25.777 --> 16:27.404
<i>Is this our girl?</i>

16:33.535 --> 16:34.994
Yeah, looks right,
but, Sarge,

16:34.994 --> 16:36.663
she looks way younger than 18.

16:36.663 --> 16:39.666
Then our charges
will be stronger.

16:39.666 --> 16:46.631
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:48.758 --> 16:50.301
Hi.

16:53.054 --> 16:54.806
You--you gonna leave?

16:54.806 --> 16:57.225
Money. I take your cash.

17:03.732 --> 17:05.442
There's 150.

17:05.442 --> 17:07.027
That's our go. Move.

17:07.027 --> 17:14.200
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:20.248 --> 17:22.208
We're made.
Crash now.

17:22.208 --> 17:24.419
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

17:24.419 --> 17:26.129
- Chicago PD!
- PD!

17:26.129 --> 17:27.547
Chicago PD!
[people scream]

17:27.547 --> 17:29.674
Let me see your hands.
Get over there.

17:29.674 --> 17:31.551
Get down, get down, get down.
Hands on the bed.

17:31.551 --> 17:33.595
- Where's Tovar?
- I got the girls.

17:34.971 --> 17:35.930
[muffled shout, loud crash]

17:35.930 --> 17:37.891
Ruz, I'm entering!

17:37.891 --> 17:40.226
[both grunting]

17:40.226 --> 17:42.896
Uh!
- [grunts]

17:42.896 --> 17:47.067
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:47.067 --> 17:48.568
Turn around.

17:48.568 --> 17:50.153
Put your hands
behind your back.

17:50.153 --> 17:51.488
Behind your back.

17:56.701 --> 17:57.869
- Tovar takes care of me.
- He takes care of you

17:59.162 --> 18:00.872
because you make his money.
- He's my boyfriend.

18:00.872 --> 18:02.707
You know this isn't
about hooking, right?

18:02.707 --> 18:04.584
We know she lived
in the same motel as you.

18:04.584 --> 18:06.127
Yeah, so?

18:09.172 --> 18:10.465
Okay.

18:10.465 --> 18:12.342
We're not wasting time.

18:14.594 --> 18:16.846
We have you for charges
of resisting arrest,

18:16.846 --> 18:19.808
assault against the police,
and sex trafficking.

18:19.808 --> 18:20.892
I'm dating those women.

18:20.892 --> 18:21.935
They're girls.

18:21.935 --> 18:23.311
And no, you're not.

18:25.146 --> 18:28.733
I don't need 'em
to make these charges.

18:28.733 --> 18:32.529
I think they will talk
when they see these photos.

18:32.529 --> 18:34.114
Uh-huh.

18:34.114 --> 18:35.532
You think I did that to her?

18:35.532 --> 18:36.783
No.

18:36.783 --> 18:38.743
I think she was making you
way too much money

18:38.743 --> 18:39.869
for you to kill her.

18:41.538 --> 18:43.415
Okay, then why am I here?

18:43.415 --> 18:44.833
'Cause I think
you know something

18:44.833 --> 18:46.126
about what happened to her.

18:46.126 --> 18:47.419
No, I don't.

18:47.419 --> 18:49.295
She was stalked,

18:49.295 --> 18:51.756
hunted like prey.

18:51.756 --> 18:54.426
This offender, he likes
to watch his victims,

18:54.426 --> 18:56.928
follow them, play with them.

18:56.928 --> 19:00.181
He likes to learn them
before he pounces.

19:01.891 --> 19:05.311
Izzy was followed,
then abducted violently,

19:05.311 --> 19:06.855
taken into the night.

19:09.858 --> 19:11.359
I'm right?

19:13.820 --> 19:15.864
Tell me what I got right.

19:19.617 --> 19:21.703
What would I get for talking?

19:23.705 --> 19:24.914
What'd you have to give him?

19:24.914 --> 19:26.332
His deal is for one count,

19:26.332 --> 19:28.877
dismisses
the underage charges.

19:28.877 --> 19:31.588
Tovar didn't know Noah,
didn't recognize him.

19:31.588 --> 19:34.007
Never noticed anyone
stalking Izzy.

19:34.007 --> 19:36.551
But he did see the abduction.

19:36.551 --> 19:39.512
Two months ago, late at night,
he hears screaming outside.

19:39.512 --> 19:41.931
Looks out his motel window.

19:41.931 --> 19:44.059
He sees someone beating Izzy.

19:44.059 --> 19:45.810
He assumes it's a john,

19:45.810 --> 19:47.979
so he goes outside
to confront him,

19:47.979 --> 19:49.105
and he filmed it all.

19:49.105 --> 19:50.565
What, for his own safety?

19:50.565 --> 19:52.776
Yeah, in case
he was ever brought in.

19:52.776 --> 19:54.194
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:54.194 --> 19:55.320
<i>[screams]</i>

19:55.320 --> 19:57.113
<i>Hey, yo.
Yo!</i>

19:57.113 --> 19:58.782
<i>What the hell are you doing?</i>

19:58.782 --> 20:00.158
<i>That's my girl!</i>

20:00.158 --> 20:01.159
<i>Get away from her!</i>

20:01.159 --> 20:03.495
[panting]

20:03.495 --> 20:05.914
Let her go!
I said, she's mine!

20:08.416 --> 20:10.001
<i>[car door slams,
engine turns over]</i>

20:10.001 --> 20:11.753
I got you on film, you bitch!

20:11.753 --> 20:14.631
[tires squealing]
You're a dead man!

20:16.841 --> 20:18.677
This guy is smart.

20:18.677 --> 20:20.553
His clothing
is indistinguishable.

20:20.553 --> 20:23.807
I mean, I can't find
a single label from any angle.

20:23.807 --> 20:26.393
Gloves and mask
are generic too.

20:26.393 --> 20:27.769
He could have
bought them anywhere.

20:27.769 --> 20:29.396
- The car?
- Nothing yet.

20:29.396 --> 20:31.272
Same story.
It's hot.

20:31.272 --> 20:33.066
Somehow staying off camera.

20:33.066 --> 20:35.110
Why a pipe for his weapon?

20:35.110 --> 20:37.195
Maybe there's something there.

20:37.195 --> 20:40.907
Pipe from a job,
his house, garage.

20:40.907 --> 20:42.492
Thought the same thing.

20:42.492 --> 20:44.744
But again, nothing
distinguishable here.

20:44.744 --> 20:47.038
I-I can't seem to get
a make or a model.

20:48.415 --> 20:50.583
There's got to be
something here.

20:50.583 --> 20:52.919
This is a good lead.

20:52.919 --> 20:55.588
Offender can't be this skilled,
this organized.

20:55.588 --> 20:57.424
We've got two abductions
caught on tape,

20:57.424 --> 20:59.092
and we have nothing to go on?

20:59.092 --> 21:01.344
- What about Maria?
- No.

21:01.344 --> 21:03.555
No reports of 911 calls
in her area.

21:03.555 --> 21:06.433
It's just like she fell
off the face of the Earth.

21:06.433 --> 21:09.019
And we still don't know
who Noah was with.

21:09.019 --> 21:11.312
There's got to be
something here.

21:13.189 --> 21:14.607
And we need more.

21:16.192 --> 21:18.028
We need way more.

21:28.329 --> 21:29.748
Noah?

21:35.170 --> 21:36.838
Hey, Noah?

21:36.838 --> 21:39.883
<i>[classical music playing
over earbuds]</i>

21:45.263 --> 21:47.265
Thank you for the phone.

21:47.265 --> 21:49.684
You're welcome.

21:57.650 --> 22:00.028
I need to talk to you,
don't I?

22:01.738 --> 22:03.031
Yeah.

22:04.532 --> 22:05.825
[music stops]
I want to give you time.

22:05.825 --> 22:07.827
You know, I know you need time.

22:07.827 --> 22:10.080
But look, Noah...

22:13.041 --> 22:16.002
This offender,

22:16.002 --> 22:18.546
he's out there right now.

22:22.509 --> 22:24.427
I don't know how.

22:24.427 --> 22:26.596
I know.

22:26.596 --> 22:29.057
If I think about it...

22:32.143 --> 22:34.396
I feel like I'm back there.

22:36.523 --> 22:38.566
Like I'm dying.

22:40.068 --> 22:41.611
Like he's dying.

22:41.611 --> 22:45.448
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

22:45.448 --> 22:48.827
And then I can't breathe.

22:48.827 --> 22:50.370
It hurts.

22:50.370 --> 22:55.333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:55.333 --> 22:57.544
[breathes deeply]

22:57.544 --> 22:59.587
I get it.

23:05.635 --> 23:08.722
You know, sometimes
you remind me of my son.

23:11.599 --> 23:13.435
And there are so many things
with him

23:13.435 --> 23:15.520
I don't like thinking about.

23:18.898 --> 23:21.484
He died.

23:21.484 --> 23:24.320
I don't like thinking
about how...

23:24.320 --> 23:25.739
it hurts.

23:27.949 --> 23:32.912
So sometimes I try not
to think about it at all.

23:35.665 --> 23:38.793
And I don't think that's right.

23:41.671 --> 23:46.134
Maybe we owe it to them
to think about things,

23:46.134 --> 23:48.636
since we're still here.

23:48.636 --> 23:55.810
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:58.146 --> 23:59.481
Okay.

24:06.738 --> 24:09.741
But can we go
somewhere else to talk?

24:09.741 --> 24:12.160
Noah, we can go anywhere.

24:12.160 --> 24:17.123
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:17.123 --> 24:20.043
[classical music playing]

24:23.880 --> 24:25.674
[sighs]

24:25.674 --> 24:28.551
I-I found this place
the first week I got here.

24:28.551 --> 24:30.762
Yeah?

24:30.762 --> 24:34.641
- Yeah.
- Yeah, it's a...

24:34.641 --> 24:36.935
really good find.
- [chuckles]

24:39.062 --> 24:42.941
The music school doesn't mind
if you sit out here.

24:42.941 --> 24:44.484
They get it.

24:44.484 --> 24:46.194
That's nice.

24:48.905 --> 24:53.326
I used to play music
in church.

24:53.326 --> 24:55.245
It was the only thing
about that place I loved.

24:55.245 --> 24:56.329
[chuckles]

24:56.329 --> 24:58.123
I'd bring Paul here.

25:00.250 --> 25:03.253
Is that who you were
with that night, Paul?

25:03.253 --> 25:06.673
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

25:06.673 --> 25:09.050
Yeah.

25:09.050 --> 25:10.427
Yeah, Paul Hansen.

25:10.427 --> 25:12.345
Okay.

25:12.345 --> 25:14.597
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:14.597 --> 25:18.268
I remember waking up...

25:18.268 --> 25:20.770
and I was tied up.

25:24.733 --> 25:27.193
I couldn't see the man.

25:28.737 --> 25:31.364
He took his mask off,
but he had these...

25:31.364 --> 25:34.784
lights in my eyes.

25:34.784 --> 25:37.996
I knew I was gonna die.

25:37.996 --> 25:41.124
And he told me I wasn't,
you know?

25:44.002 --> 25:46.546
He said I had a chance to live.

25:46.546 --> 25:48.923
He gave me one call.

25:48.923 --> 25:52.260
He said to call the person
I loved most in the world.

25:53.887 --> 25:57.098
He told me to call Paul.

26:00.226 --> 26:01.936
I didn't want to die.

26:05.440 --> 26:07.942
And it--it was a trick.

26:09.652 --> 26:11.905
But I didn't want to die,
so I called Paul.

26:11.905 --> 26:13.990
Yeah, I would have done
the same thing.

26:13.990 --> 26:15.283
No. No.

26:17.452 --> 26:21.373
He told me to tell him
that I had a surprise for him.

26:25.293 --> 26:26.878
Paul came.

26:29.422 --> 26:32.550
Then the man attacked him.

26:32.550 --> 26:36.388
He tied him up, and then he--

26:36.388 --> 26:37.430
[sobs]

26:37.430 --> 26:39.432
He hurt you both.

26:39.432 --> 26:41.851
Yeah. Okay, okay.

26:43.311 --> 26:44.813
Take your time.

26:46.147 --> 26:49.484
The man got some phone call,

26:49.484 --> 26:51.945
so he had to step away.

26:53.905 --> 26:56.366
And he didn't know
that one of my ties was loose,

26:56.366 --> 26:57.742
so I got away.

27:00.495 --> 27:02.038
But Paul--

27:03.790 --> 27:04.874
He was dead?

27:04.874 --> 27:07.085
I felt for a pulse.

27:07.085 --> 27:08.461
He was gone.

27:08.461 --> 27:10.338
Okay.

27:10.338 --> 27:12.215
I ran.

27:13.675 --> 27:15.093
I'm glad you ran.

27:15.093 --> 27:16.678
It's a good thing
you got out of there.

27:16.678 --> 27:19.806
[moans]
I left him.

27:22.100 --> 27:24.144
I kissed him goodbye,
and I left.

27:27.689 --> 27:30.191
I love him...

27:30.191 --> 27:32.193
and I left him.

27:32.193 --> 27:37.240
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:37.240 --> 27:39.451
It was all my fault.
- No.

27:39.451 --> 27:41.244
- For loving him.
- No.

27:41.244 --> 27:42.954
- I'm being punished.
- No, no, no.

27:42.954 --> 27:45.582
No, no, he was taken away
from me because I'm wrong.

27:45.582 --> 27:46.833
No, no, you're not wrong.

27:46.833 --> 27:48.585
Hey.
- I just want him back.

27:48.585 --> 27:50.003
Hey, hey, I know.

27:50.003 --> 27:52.005
I get it.
- [sobbing]

27:52.005 --> 27:55.091
Noah, listen to me.
You did good, okay?

27:56.551 --> 27:58.219
Thank you for telling me.

28:01.097 --> 28:03.183
That's it, just take a breath.

28:03.183 --> 28:04.684
You did great.

28:04.684 --> 28:11.900
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:23.203 --> 28:24.162
Sounds like Paul
was his boyfriend.

28:25.288 --> 28:26.331
I mean, they haven't known
each other long,

28:26.331 --> 28:27.374
just since Noah
arrived in Chicago.

28:27.374 --> 28:28.333
We ran him.

28:28.333 --> 28:29.918
Paul Hansen, 24,
Chicago resident,

28:29.918 --> 28:31.169
in and out of homeless shelters

28:31.169 --> 28:32.837
and halfway homes
in the past two years.

28:32.837 --> 28:34.255
Two pops for prostitution.

28:34.255 --> 28:36.216
Looks like he was doing
what he needed to to get by.

28:36.216 --> 28:38.134
Sex work is our common link
after all.

28:38.134 --> 28:39.886
And no one
reported Paul missing?

28:39.886 --> 28:41.554
No, and no pops
in any morgues

28:41.554 --> 28:42.639
or hospitals in the area.

28:42.639 --> 28:44.015
We're working on last knowns,

28:44.015 --> 28:46.393
in-service calls,
phone records, you name it.

28:46.393 --> 28:48.311
Hey, let's run that photo
by Tovar.

28:48.311 --> 28:50.230
Yeah, I did.
Tovar didn't know him,

28:50.230 --> 28:51.606
never seen him on any tracks.

28:51.606 --> 28:52.857
Okay, we loop in Vice?

28:52.857 --> 28:54.567
Yes, they're culling
their records now.

28:54.567 --> 28:57.112
All right, let's also have
them run anyone in their system

28:57.112 --> 28:59.239
that also pops
for violent priors.

28:59.239 --> 29:02.075
If our offender's choosing
his victims based on sex work,

29:02.075 --> 29:03.326
chances are, Vice knows him.
- No.

29:03.326 --> 29:04.869
No, no, no,
it's more than just that.

29:04.869 --> 29:08.081
He--he's choosing them because
they have someone they love.

29:08.081 --> 29:09.624
The Pereda sisters,
Noah and Paul,

29:09.624 --> 29:10.917
they loved each other,

29:10.917 --> 29:13.253
had deep connection.

29:13.253 --> 29:16.131
And then he forces them
to watch each other die,

29:16.131 --> 29:19.426
seeps that connection
out of them,

29:19.426 --> 29:22.095
steals it for himself.

29:22.095 --> 29:24.973
Yo, I found Paul
on an escort site.

29:24.973 --> 29:26.599
It looked like he was
working independently,

29:26.599 --> 29:29.352
but I found a nexus
between him and Izzy.

29:29.352 --> 29:30.812
A judge?

29:30.812 --> 29:34.441
Sarge, believe it or not,
both Izzy and Paul's files

29:34.441 --> 29:36.484
came across
Judge Balen's desk.

29:36.484 --> 29:37.736
Could be coincidental.

29:37.736 --> 29:39.446
No. Look at that.

29:39.446 --> 29:42.198
The judge's number pops
on both of their phone records,

29:42.198 --> 29:44.200
and the same number is used
on a dummy profile

29:44.200 --> 29:46.119
to access both escort sites.

29:46.119 --> 29:48.246
That man's a john.

29:48.246 --> 29:50.498
That's how Tovar ID'd him.

29:50.498 --> 29:52.375
It could fit.

29:52.375 --> 29:55.086
Balen would have acute
knowledge of law enforcement.

29:55.086 --> 29:57.088
It explains the avoidance
of traffic cams,

29:57.088 --> 29:58.590
pristine crime scenes.

29:58.590 --> 30:00.467
He could easily trace
his victims through the system,

30:00.467 --> 30:03.345
ID them based on files
that come across his desk.

30:03.345 --> 30:04.763
Let's go.

30:04.763 --> 30:07.766
<i>[tense music]</i>

30:07.766 --> 30:11.728
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:11.728 --> 30:13.313
Like I said,
he's in chambers.

30:13.313 --> 30:15.106
And like I said, I'll wait.

30:15.106 --> 30:17.525
I usually don't leave people
unattended in his office.

30:17.525 --> 30:19.402
Would you like
to see my badge again?

30:19.402 --> 30:21.071
No. No, of course not.

30:21.071 --> 30:22.655
Right this way.

30:22.655 --> 30:29.579
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:35.377 --> 30:37.087
I don't understand.
What's going on?

30:37.087 --> 30:38.630
You can't come in here.

30:38.630 --> 30:39.964
Why can't I call my husband?

30:39.964 --> 30:41.966
- Ma'am.
- What? Wait.

30:41.966 --> 30:43.718
This has to be
a misunderstanding.

30:43.718 --> 30:45.011
What is going on?

30:45.011 --> 30:46.221
Here's our search warrant,
ma'am, okay?

30:46.221 --> 30:47.347
How about we step aside

30:47.347 --> 30:49.516
and I can talk you
through it, okay?

30:49.516 --> 30:56.398
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:11.329 --> 31:13.248
- Detective?
- Sergeant.

31:14.541 --> 31:15.917
Is everything okay?

31:15.917 --> 31:17.043
Is my wife all right?

31:17.043 --> 31:19.546
Oh, your wife is fine.

31:19.546 --> 31:21.172
I'm here for you.

31:21.172 --> 31:22.382
How can I help you?

31:22.382 --> 31:23.550
I'm happy to help you
with warrants--

31:23.550 --> 31:25.260
No, I'm here for you.

31:25.260 --> 31:27.178
For you.

31:27.178 --> 31:29.431
And Izzy and Maria Pereda,

31:29.431 --> 31:31.099
Noah Gorman,

31:31.099 --> 31:32.475
Paul Hansen.

31:34.561 --> 31:35.729
I don't understand.

31:35.729 --> 31:37.147
I think you do.

31:37.147 --> 31:44.320
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:02.672 --> 32:04.049
Evidence officer.

32:04.049 --> 32:05.717
<i>Yeah, just a sec.</i>

32:17.812 --> 32:19.105
[clears throat]

32:21.441 --> 32:23.151
If you're here
to accuse me of something,

32:23.151 --> 32:25.236
I hope you've thought
of the consequences.

32:25.236 --> 32:26.654
<i>Boss, we have it.</i>

32:26.654 --> 32:28.156
<i>Take him.</i>

32:28.156 --> 32:30.784
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:30.784 --> 32:32.410
Copy you, Adam.

32:34.245 --> 32:37.165
Are you--you can't
be referring to me.

32:37.165 --> 32:38.291
Take--take me where?
- Yeah, I'm not gonna

32:38.291 --> 32:41.294
play games with you.

32:41.294 --> 32:43.963
I'll give you one chance
to talk to me here,

32:43.963 --> 32:46.132
where it's comfortable,

32:46.132 --> 32:47.634
before the press get involved,

32:47.634 --> 32:49.094
before your family,

32:49.094 --> 32:51.596
before you're sitting
in a cold box.

32:51.596 --> 32:53.848
One chance right now.

32:53.848 --> 32:55.892
Go ahead.
What do you have to say?

32:55.892 --> 32:57.143
Talk.

32:57.143 --> 32:59.979
Come on, talk.
Go ahead.

32:59.979 --> 33:01.314
Go ahead.

33:01.314 --> 33:03.233
I'd like to call my lawyer.

33:07.028 --> 33:10.240
Turn around.

33:10.240 --> 33:13.326
Give me your hands.
- [huffs]

33:15.620 --> 33:18.164
Well, I'm not bringing
those photos in here,

33:18.164 --> 33:20.375
but you know what they are.

33:20.375 --> 33:24.337
We found them in your house,
in your cabinet, Judge.

33:24.337 --> 33:27.507
<i>I mean, you know
the charging guidelines.</i>

33:27.507 --> 33:30.343
Child pornography
is a Class X felony.

33:30.343 --> 33:31.928
My client has no comment
about any of that.

33:31.928 --> 33:33.221
No, see, I think he does.

33:33.221 --> 33:35.807
I think he wants to talk,
maybe have a good cry.

33:35.807 --> 33:37.017
I mean, you should let him.

33:37.017 --> 33:38.351
You feel pretty bad,
don't you, Judge?

33:38.351 --> 33:41.312
- This is not productive.
- You need a good cry?

33:42.689 --> 33:46.359
You want to avoid
the child porn?

33:46.359 --> 33:49.320
Okay, we can come back to that.

33:49.320 --> 33:51.906
Let's talk
about the prostitute

33:51.906 --> 33:54.242
that I can prove
you frequented...

33:56.536 --> 33:57.954
Who is now dead.

33:57.954 --> 33:59.581
She's dead?
What is this?

33:59.581 --> 34:00.874
She's dead,

34:00.874 --> 34:02.208
along with her sister...

34:02.208 --> 34:04.210
[cell phone buzzes]

34:06.004 --> 34:08.256
And Paul Hansen.

34:08.256 --> 34:10.342
No. Wait, wait.

34:10.342 --> 34:11.551
Yes, I know him--
- I can't help you

34:11.551 --> 34:13.053
if you continue
to ignore my advice.

34:13.053 --> 34:14.304
I know you know Paul Hansen.

34:14.304 --> 34:15.805
His case came across your desk.

34:15.805 --> 34:17.807
You got his phone number.
[cell phone buzzing]

34:17.807 --> 34:19.267
I mean, you kept track of him.

34:22.187 --> 34:25.231
I mean, you liked Paul Hansen
for some reason, didn't you?

34:25.231 --> 34:27.359
He was kind.
He was sweet.

34:27.359 --> 34:29.402
And you liked him.

34:29.402 --> 34:31.738
But he didn't want a real
connection with you, did he?

34:31.738 --> 34:33.865
- No. No.
- No, he loved someone else.

34:33.865 --> 34:35.283
He didn't love you.
[cell phone buzzing]

34:35.283 --> 34:36.910
And you wanted it.

34:36.910 --> 34:38.912
You wanted that for yourself,
didn't you?

34:38.912 --> 34:40.330
Please.

34:41.998 --> 34:43.917
You wanted to know what
it felt like, right, Judge,

34:43.917 --> 34:45.627
to be loved that way?

34:48.254 --> 34:50.090
Hey.

34:50.090 --> 34:51.758
Wha--No-Noah.

34:51.758 --> 34:53.635
Noah, slow down.

34:53.635 --> 34:55.261
Slow down.

34:55.261 --> 34:57.389
No--Noah, I--I--
I can't understand you.

34:57.389 --> 34:59.265
We have a bad connection.

34:59.265 --> 35:01.142
Can you say that again?

35:01.142 --> 35:02.977
Now, what's going on?

35:02.977 --> 35:04.604
<i>What if I was wrong?</i>

35:04.604 --> 35:06.231
<i>What if he was never
really dead?</i>

35:06.231 --> 35:07.816
<i>I think he's okay.</i>

35:07.816 --> 35:09.359
<i>I don't have
to live without him.</i>

35:09.359 --> 35:11.236
Wait, okay, Noah,
where are you right now?

35:11.236 --> 35:12.487
Are you still at my house?

35:12.487 --> 35:14.572
<i>No. I had to sneak out.</i>

35:14.572 --> 35:15.990
<i>I went out the window.</i>

35:15.990 --> 35:17.409
<i>He told me to.</i>

35:17.409 --> 35:18.618
<i>He said he got away.</i>

35:18.618 --> 35:20.745
<i>I was wrong.
He's not dead.</i>

35:20.745 --> 35:23.164
Paul?
P-Paul told you he's not dead?

35:23.164 --> 35:25.375
<i>Yeah.
I'm going to meet him now.</i>

35:25.375 --> 35:27.293
<i>He--he told me where to go.</i>

35:27.293 --> 35:29.212
<i>I get to be with him again.</i>

35:29.212 --> 35:30.547
<i>I get him back.</i>

35:30.547 --> 35:32.340
Noah.

35:32.340 --> 35:34.134
Noah, how did Paul
tell you that?

35:34.134 --> 35:35.427
<i>He texted me.</i>

35:35.427 --> 35:37.470
<i>He texted me from his phone.</i>

35:37.470 --> 35:39.723
<i>He's alive.
He's okay.</i>

35:44.936 --> 35:46.062
Listen to me, Noah.
This doesn't make sense.

35:48.314 --> 35:50.150
Paul is dead.

35:50.150 --> 35:51.484
Look, you took his pulse.

35:51.484 --> 35:53.319
You said you knew for sure.

35:53.319 --> 35:55.155
<i>But maybe I was wrong.</i>

35:55.155 --> 35:56.322
<i>I want him back.</i>

35:56.322 --> 35:57.490
Yeah, can I get
an emergency ping

35:57.490 --> 35:58.742
on Noah Gorman's
cell phone number?

35:58.742 --> 36:00.326
All right, tell me
where you are right now.

36:00.326 --> 36:01.619
<i>He said to meet him
in the woods.</i>

36:01.619 --> 36:03.955
No, no, no, no.
No. Listen to me.

36:03.955 --> 36:05.373
I need you to leave.

36:05.373 --> 36:07.125
I want you to go back
to my house.

36:07.125 --> 36:09.127
I'm--I'm gonna meet you there.
- Yeah, Noah Gorman.

36:09.127 --> 36:10.295
Can you tell me how long
it's been active?

36:10.295 --> 36:12.047
Did Judge Balen
have access to a phone?

36:12.047 --> 36:14.507
Besides calling his lawyer,
hell no, I verified it.

36:14.507 --> 36:16.217
All right, send me his
coordinates when you have them.

36:16.217 --> 36:17.886
- Copy.
- Noah.

36:17.886 --> 36:19.262
Noah, did you leave?

36:19.262 --> 36:21.931
<i>No. I have to find him.</i>

36:21.931 --> 36:24.184
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

36:24.184 --> 36:26.728
[tires screech]

36:26.728 --> 36:28.813
I need you to leave.
I need you--

36:28.813 --> 36:31.358
I need you to get somewhere
with people right now.

36:31.358 --> 36:33.651
<i>No, it's Paul.
He's alive.</i>

36:33.651 --> 36:35.195
<i>He is. He has to be.</i>
- Noah, no.

36:35.195 --> 36:37.822
No, you want him to be.

36:37.822 --> 36:39.574
Paul isn't alive.

36:39.574 --> 36:41.868
He's dead.
You know that.

36:41.868 --> 36:43.453
You saw that.

36:43.453 --> 36:45.872
Look, this isn't Paul, Noah.

36:45.872 --> 36:48.124
Someone is luring you.

36:48.124 --> 36:50.877
Okay, I need you to go
right now.

36:50.877 --> 36:52.545
<i>Sarge, Noah's coordinates
are pinging</i>

36:52.545 --> 36:53.922
<i>on the east side
of the forest preserve.</i>

36:53.922 --> 36:55.507
<i>I can't get you
any closer than that.</i>

36:55.507 --> 36:57.926
All right, copy. Just ping
Paul's phone right now.

36:57.926 --> 36:59.135
<i>I'm on it.</i>

36:59.135 --> 37:01.388
Noah, are you still there?

37:01.388 --> 37:03.348
Noah.
<i>- I just want him back.</i>

37:03.348 --> 37:04.724
<i>I don't want to be alone.</i>

37:04.724 --> 37:06.142
<i>I just--I just want
to see him again.</i>

37:06.142 --> 37:07.686
Noah, I know you do.

37:07.686 --> 37:09.354
I know that.

37:09.354 --> 37:11.523
Just turn around for me, okay?

37:11.523 --> 37:12.941
I'll be there--
<i>- [grunts]</i>

37:12.941 --> 37:14.776
<i>[line beeps]</i>

37:14.776 --> 37:18.029
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:18.029 --> 37:20.073
<i>The caller you have reached
is not available.</i>

37:20.073 --> 37:21.241
[engine revs]

37:21.241 --> 37:28.248
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:28.248 --> 37:31.751
<i>[tense music]</i>

37:31.751 --> 37:38.717
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:39.676 --> 37:40.969
Noah!

37:45.557 --> 37:48.309
Noah, call out
if you can hear me!

38:07.495 --> 38:08.830
[branch snaps]

38:10.915 --> 38:12.625
[leaves rustle]

38:24.888 --> 38:26.431
Noah!

38:35.273 --> 38:36.608
Noah!

38:38.026 --> 38:40.278
Noah Gorman, call out!

38:40.278 --> 38:42.530
Chicago police!

38:45.950 --> 38:48.870
Noah! Call out!

38:52.749 --> 38:53.958
Noah!

38:56.044 --> 38:57.879
Noah, can you hear us?

38:57.879 --> 39:01.508
Noah!

39:01.508 --> 39:08.682
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:16.606 --> 39:18.566
[distantly] Noah!

39:18.566 --> 39:20.902
Noah, call out!

39:57.689 --> 40:00.775
[indistinct radio chatter]

40:02.485 --> 40:03.903
Boss, we just
got confirmation

40:03.903 --> 40:06.114
that both Paul and Noah's
phones are off now.

40:06.114 --> 40:08.408
It was Paul's phone
that texted him?

40:08.408 --> 40:10.285
Yeah.

40:10.285 --> 40:12.662
Phone records indicate Noah's
been calling Paul's phone

40:12.662 --> 40:14.289
from the new phone you got him.

40:14.289 --> 40:18.043
We think he just wanted to hear
his voicemail, hear his voice.

40:18.043 --> 40:20.253
How the offender
got Noah's number.

40:20.253 --> 40:21.463
Yeah.

40:22.672 --> 40:24.716
There's no cameras or PODs
in the entryway,

40:24.716 --> 40:26.885
but we're checking
all traffic cams in the area.

40:28.011 --> 40:29.346
Judge Balen?

40:29.346 --> 40:30.972
Judge has a concrete alibi

40:30.972 --> 40:32.599
for the time
of Izzy's abduction,

40:32.599 --> 40:34.768
but he confessed
to the solicitation charges.

40:34.768 --> 40:36.394
Sex charges are airtight,

40:36.394 --> 40:38.396
so he's gonna have some
legal troubles in his future--

40:38.396 --> 40:40.482
<i>I got something.</i>

40:41.816 --> 40:44.152
Yeah, there's more over here.

40:44.152 --> 40:47.113
<i>[somber music]</i>

40:47.113 --> 40:53.787
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:13.056 --> 41:19.979
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:29.614 --> 41:36.746
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:18.413 --> 42:21.583
[wolf howls]
